hopobject.body: I'm sorry, I'm not interested generico del viagra en chile The U.S. economy was not built on big banks – we left that mistake to others, until recently. But people running the largest U.S. financial firms managed to get the rules changed from the 1980s and, as a result, their firms bulked up and greatly expanded their range of activities during the big credit boom that led to the crisis of 2008. Today's behemoths are those that became even bigger as a result of the bailouts and other forms of government support they received during that crisis.
